Discrete Evanescent-Barrier Amplitude Suppression on Cl(3)/Z^3
========================================================================

Retained scope:
  Theorem A: discrete lattice transfer-matrix bound
             |G| <= C exp[-sum_i ln lambda_+(i)],
             lambda_+(i) = (u_i + sqrt(u_i^2 - 4))/2,
             u_i = 2 + (V_i - E)/t.
  Theorem B: Schwarzschild interior tortoise-length identity
             L* = R_S ln((R_S - R_min)/eps) + eps + R_min - R_S.

Open conditional (C-rate):  order-one per-unit-tortoise-length rate
  lower bound required to convert theorems A + B into the Planck-unit
  astrophysical exponent exp[-(R_S/l_P) ln(R_S/R_min)] carried by the
  bounded GW-echo null companion.  NOT on the retained surface.

